Uses of Class
kodkod.ast.IntExpression

  • Packages that use IntExpression 
    Package Description
    kodkod.ast
    Contains classes for creating Kodkod formulas, expressions, and integer expressions.
    kodkod.ast.visitor
    Contains visitors for Kodkod formulas, expressions, and integer expressions.
    kodkod.engine
    Provides classes for analyzing and evaluating Kodkod ASTs with respect to finite bounds or instances.
    kodkod.engine.fol2sat
    Provides a facade for translating, evaluating, and approximating Kodkod formulas, expressions, and int expressions with respect to a given Bounds (or Instance) and Options.

      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  BinaryIntExpression
      A binary integer expression such as x + y.
      class  ExprToIntCast
      An IntExpression representing the cardinality of an Expression or the sum of all the integer atoms contained in the expression.
      class  IfIntExpression
      An int expression whose value depends on the truth of a condition.
      class  IntConstant
      An integer constant (literal).
      class  NaryIntExpression
      A int expression with more than two children, composed with an nary operator.
      class  SumExpression
      Denotes the integer obtained by summing the values of an iteger expression ie for all values of a scalar x drawn from a set e.
